article.headline: Hofstra 65, James Madison 61
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) -- Aurimas Kieza had 19 points and 10 rebounds to lead Hofstra to its third straight victory, 65-61 over James Madison on Saturday. Loren Stokes added 12 points for the Pride (13-13, 9-7 Colonial Athletic Association). Dwayne Broyles scored 20 points for the Dukes (7-18, 3-13), whose losing streak was extended to four games, while Cavell Johnson had 16 points and Daniel Freeman added 15. Freeman hit two jumpers as James Madison made its first four shots in taking an 8-0 lead. The Pride responded with a 14-4 run, capped by a jumper by Stokes with 11:31 left, to gain their first lead. Johnson then scored seven consecutive points to put James Madison ahead 19-14. Hofstra outscored the Dukes 19-9 over the final 7:44 to take a 39-30 halftime lead. Kieza scored seven points in the run. Johnson had seven points in an 11-2 run to get the Dukes within 45-43 with 10:40 to play. But Kieza had a 3-pointer and a jumper as Hofstra held the Dukes scoreless over the next 4:12 to take a 55-43 lead with 6:28 left. Freeman then accounted for nine points during a 20-4 run as James Madison made it 63-59 with 1:27 to go. Kieza made the second of two free throws to make it 64-59 with 59 seconds left. James Madison got as close as 64-61 on two foul shots by Ray Barbosa with 19 seconds remaining.
